-- BMW Hires Temporary Workers, May Expand Working Hours, Handelsblatt Says
-- Andreas Cremer
-- 2010-06-24T05:08:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/bmw-hires-temporary-workers-may-expand-working-hours-handelsblatt-says.html

          
          
             Bayerische Motoren Werke AG  is
hiring temporary workers and may expand working hours to meet
growing demand for luxury cars,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing
personnel chief  Harald Krueger .  
 Munich-based BMW is also mulling shorter holiday closures
as capacity utilization at some of its factories is “very
good,” the newspaper cited Krueger as saying.  
